The paper proposes a novel feature descriptor for instance search that is built upon a salient instance region activated by a layer-wise back-propagation process. This process involves a pre-trained CNN originally used for classification, indicating a focus on computer vision (CV) techniques. The paper also mentions experiments on instance and image search tasks, suggesting information retrieval (IR) as another relevant sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques and the focus on feature representation make machine learning (LG) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper's emphasis on pattern recognition and classification aligns with multimedia (MM) and artificial intelligence (AI) sub-categories.
